  "name": "RPlog_Spycraft_-_The_Viewing",
  "title": "Casing the Auction Block",
  "summary": "Posing as a buying party under cover names, the intelligence team gathers in an opulent Nar Shaddaa casino to attend the slave auction's preview. Their Duros fixer Zalla distributes forged identities and credit accounts, casting Wrexan as the chief buyer 'Mr. Greene' and the others as his staff, while pilot Tiaryn adopts the alias 'Pilot Violet' and a flustered gambler named Valya keeps awkwardly crossing their path. Led by Zalla past tight security and down a long turbolift, the group enters a cavernous holding floor where captives of every age and species are caged in wire mesh and paraded across an auction block. While maintaining their cover with drinks and bored chatter, Kelnas and Wrexan map the cameras, security droids, and the cargo lift at the back, Tiaryn counts the captives in each pen, and Siarra assesses the cages' flimsy locks. Their reconnaissance complete and the count matching their intel, the team disperses in pairs on Zalla's advice to leave slowly and unremarkably, regrouping later at the warehouse.",
